<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLL ON SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Only the tobacco industry could have the gall to poll 1,500 adults (less than 
one in 100,000 or exactly 30 per state) and announce that a "majority" of 
Americans do not support higher cigarette taxes or tougher anti-smoking 
legislation (Tobacco Institute ad, Business, Jan. 9). 
</P>
<P>
If so, how come Proposition 99 passed despite a massive and misleading campaign 
by tobacco companies? 
</P>
<P>
The statistics showing the damage and financial burdens smokers inflict on 
others as well as themselves are too dreary and familiar to bear repeating -- 
not that they'd impress an industry that still denies smoking causes lung 
cancer. 
</P>
<P>
MAX SHAPIRO 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
