<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN and STEVE WEINSTEIN, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking of trees, famed graphic artist Peter Max donated an original 
acrylic-on-canvas painting portraying two trees to Mayor Tom Bradley, who 
accepted the Max original on behalf of TreePeople, a Los Angeles-based 
conservation group that is organizing a program to plant as many as 5 million 
trees across the city over the next five years. Though TreePeople officials 
have yet to decide what to do with the painting, it will either be used as a 
symbol for the planting campaign or auctioned to help raise money for the 
multimillion dollar effort. ALEENE MacMINN and STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
