<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN and STEVE WEINSTEIN, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Gone With the Wind" will be playing in theaters across the country this year 
to celebrate its golden anniversary. MGM/UA is booking the 1939 classic in 
select theaters to give fans "the rare chance to view the film in its original 
glory and splendor," says Turner Entertainment President Roger Mayer. "GWTW" 
will be shown at the Los Angeles County Museum of Art on Feb. 11 as a benefit 
for the museum's film department. The tab: $75. The re-release engagement of 
the film will begin at Radio City Music Hall in New York City on Jan. 30-31. 
ALEENE MacMINN and STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
