</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire in a three-story rooming house in Yonkers, N.Y., killed seven people and 
injured at least eight others, including five firefighters, authorities said. A 
woman was in guarded condition at St. Joseph's Hospital, a nursing supervisor 
said. Two badly burned bodies were found just behind the front door, Fire 
Commissioner William McLaughlin said, adding that the door opened outward and 
officials were uncertain why the two could not escape. Investigators were 
seeking the cause of the blaze. 
</P>
