<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR KILLED WHEN THEY FALL INTO ICE-COVERED LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NORTH BANGOR, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman and three children who fell into an ice-covered lake Sunday died after 
at least 30 minutes exposure to the frigid water, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Killed were Carolee Strunk, 28, and her children April Strunk, 9, and Jared 
Strunk, 5. Also killed was family friend Sarah Bowers, 8. 
</P>
<P>
The four fell through the ice about 150 yards from shore and eventually were 
pulled out, along with an unidentified fisherman who fell in going to their 
assistance. The fisherman was treated at a hospital and released. 
</P>
