<DOCID> 6171 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
January 16, 1989, Monday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 2; Column 4; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
88 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY, 10, DIES AFTER BIKE IS HIT BY TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 10-year-old Poway boy was struck and killed by a pickup truck while riding 
his bicycle, authorities reported. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Wood was bicycling in the 12400 block of McFeron Road about 3 p.m. 
Saturday when he was hit by a pickup truck driven by Scott Ball, 29, of Poway, 
according to Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Cunningham. 
</P>
<P>
The boy was flown by Life Flight helicopter to Children's Hospital, where he 
later died from injuries, Cunningham said. 
</P>
<P>
No charges are planned against Ball, but an investigation is continuing, 
Cunningham said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
