<P>
BOSTON CO. SAYS PROFITS OVERSTATED BY $30 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boston Co.'s profits for the first three quarters of 1988 were overstated by 
$30 million, more than twice as high as preliminary estimates, officials with 
the investment firm said. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc., Boston Co.'s parent firm, said 
Friday that a committee of outside auditors and Shearson officers arrived at 
the higher estimate after an examination of Boston's financial position. 
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the panel was trying to determine who was responsible for 
the overstatement. 
</P>
