<P>
MOTORCYCLE OFFICER STRUCK AT STOPLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Ana motorcycle officer was rammed while stopped at a red light early 
Sunday by a man suspected of drunk driving, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The officer, Dan McDermott, was stopped at 1st and Standard streets about 12:30 
a.m. when he was struck by a car driven by Santa Ana resident Alcaraz Orozco 
Olegario, Police Sgt. Collie Provence said. 
</P>
<P>
McDermott suffered cuts and bruises and was taken to Fountain Valley Regional 
Hospital and Medical Center, where he was treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
Orozco was arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving and was being held at 
the Orange County Jail in lieu of $10,000 bail, Provence said. 
</P>
