<HEADLINE>
<P>
EVANS WINS RACE AT LONG BEACH EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Janet Evans, who won three gold medals in last summer's Olympics, won the 
400-meter individual medley Sunday at the Southern California Swimming Q-Meet 
at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Evans, of Placentia, finished in 4:12.81. The meet concludes today with Evans 
swimming the 1,650-meter freestyle. Preliminary heats start at 9 a.m. with the 
finals at 5 p.m. 
</P>
