<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWEDEN'S SVAN WINS NORDIC SKIING EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NOVE MESTO, Czechoslovakia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gunde Svan of Sweden won a Nordic ski cross-country event Sunday and widened 
his lead in World Cup standings after six races this season. 
</P>
<P>
The double Olympic winner in Calgary covered the distance, contested in 
classical style, in 1 hour 17 minutes 57.7 seconds. Svan also took the first 
place in the 15-kilometer free style event Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Paal-Gunar Mikkelsplass of Norway came in second in 1:19:39.7 and his teammate, 
Vergard Ulvang, tied for third place with East Germany's Holger Bauroth in 
1:20:07.4. 
</P>
<P>
Terje Langli of Norway finished fifth in 1:20:25 and Czechoslovakia's Martin 
Petrasek took the sixth place in 1:20:35.4. 
</P>
