<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS FULLERTON TO MEET NO. 11 LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton, which has 6 straight losses after a 5-1 start, won't find 
it any easier tonight when the Titans play 11th-ranked Nevada Las Vegas in the 
Thomas &amp; Mack Center at 8:05. 
</P>
<P>
The Runnin' Rebels (11-2) have won 9 straight since losing to Arizona Dec. 10. 
</P>
<P>
UNLV has lost to Fullerton only twice in 20 meetings, and has won the past 14. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels are led by center David Butler and guard Greg Anthony, each 
averaging 14 points a game. Forward Stacey Augmon is averaging 13 points a 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton has 3 players averaging in double figures, led by Cedric Ceballos at 
19 points a game. Mark Hill averages 15 and Derek Jones 12. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
