<P>
GUNMAN YIELDS AFTER 6-HOUR SIEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A gunman surrendered early today to end a six-hour standoff with authorities 
who surrounded his Hermosa Beach home after he fired a gun during an argument 
with his wife, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Two young children were found asleep and unharmed in a bedroom of the home at 
736 Monterey Blvd. following the surrender of their father, Michael Barnum, 32, 
at 6 a.m., police Cmdr. Anthony Altfeld said. The incident began shortly after 
midnight when police received a call from a neighbor who had heard the gunshot. 
When officers arrived, they saw Barnum standing in his doorway, holding a 
semiautomatic handgun, Altfeld said. The Sheriff's Department sent its Special 
Weapons Team while other officers urged the man to surrender. 
</P>
</TEXT>
