<P>
IRAN EXECUTES 23 DRUG SMUGGLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATHENS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iranian authorities executed 23 people on charges of smuggling narcotics into 
the country, bringing to 47 the number executed on drug charges since Jan. 1, 
the official Islamic Republic News Agency said today. The latest executions 
came amid an intensified campaign against narcotics trafficking, especially 
smugglers hauling opium, heroin and marijuana from across the Pakistani and 
Afghan borders. 
</P>
